# stack-flutter — Flutter 3.x

## What it is

Google's cross-platform UI framework. Compiles Dart to native iOS / Android (and web/desktop, which we don't target).

## When I choose it

- Cross-platform mobile-first app, solo dev, real-time + native APIs needed.
- Want one codebase, near-native perf.

## When I avoid it

- Pure web product.
- Apps that need bleeding-edge native SDK access on day-1 (Flutter lags ~6 months on new iOS/Android APIs).

## Conventions I follow

- Stateless widgets by default. Stateful only when local mutable state is essential.
- Side-effects in Notifier.build (Riverpod) or behind a controller — never in build().
- const constructors everywhere the analyzer suggests.
- No print() in production. Use dart:developer log.
- Strict mode, sound null safety, all flutter_lints + custom rules in analysis_options.yaml.
- Theming: custom ThemeData + ThemeExtension. NO default Material 3.

## Common gotchas

- Hot reload misses ThemeData / static const changes — restart.
- ListView.builder is the only correct way for long lists.
- Image caching: use cached_network_image, not Image.network.

